@startuml epicd-runtime-deployment
' epicd — RUNTIME deployment: supervisor · per-pipeline drivers · workers (the "monitor" side).
' Companion to the class diagrams (which stop at the interface layer). Shows how the
' Claude Code plugin (E5 skills) + engine run at runtime, and the baime→epicd correspondence.
' Grounded in: execution-class.puml, authoring-refine-class.puml, human-operations-activity.puml,
' and baime's scan-loop.js / Monitor / .caps / .active-agents (reference implementation).

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam node {
  BorderColor #555555
  BackgroundColor #E8F0FE
}
skinparam component {
  BorderColor #555555
  BackgroundColor #FFF3E0
}
skinparam database {
  BorderColor #555555
  BackgroundColor #E1BEE7
}

title epicd — runtime deployment (supervisor · driver-per-pipeline · workers · spawn seam)

actor "Human\n(gate owner)" as Human

node "Claude Code harness  (Monitor host)" as Harness {
  component "**supervisor**\n(persistent; singleton reap;\nbaime: Monitor+scan-loop)" as Sup
  component "**execution driver**\nInterpreter.scan → item-ready\n(baime: --mode ready)" as ExecD
  component "**authoring driver** <<planned E7>>\n(RefiningHandler)\n(baime: --mode draft)" as AuthD
  component "operation skills\nrun (epicd-run skill)\npropose · promote · inbox · init <<planned E5>>" as Ops
  Sup --> ExecD : hosts (1 per pipeline_id)
  Sup --> AuthD : hosts
}

node "git worktree  (one per claimed task)" as WT {
  component "**execute worker**\nfeature/chore Agent →\nengine.complete()" as ExecW
  component "**refine worker** <<planned E7>>\n(RefineStrategy + reviewer)" as RefW
}

database "IssueSource\nbacklog/*.md\n(pipeline_id + bare phase)" as Src
component "**Coordinator** (claims)\nsoak: .caps / .active-agents\n→ engine claim registry" as Coord
database "gate-event log (E2)" as GEL

' --- drivers: scan + dispatch + the SPAWN SEAM ---
ExecD --> Src : scan (actor(phase)=machine ∧ no claim)
AuthD --> Src : scan
ExecD ..> ExecW : item-ready → **worker skill spawns Agent**
AuthD ..> RefW  : item-ready → spawn
ExecD --> Coord : claim / release
AuthD --> Coord : claim / release

' --- worker completion (engine-owned tail; worker may NOT self-write done) ---
ExecW --> Src : engine.complete() → adjudicate DoD (ENG-8) → merge under lock (ENG-3)
RefW  --> Src : append refine_log / advance phase (promote→Backlog · escalate→needs-human)
RefW  ..> GEL : reviewer verdict / gate events

' --- human operations (act only on actor=human rows) ---
Human --> Ops
Ops --> Src : propose (→Draft) · promote (Backlog→Ready)
Ops --> GEL : inbox (gate-review: approve/reject/escalate)
Ops ..> Sup : run (arm supervisor+drivers) · init (bootstrap pipelines[])

note bottom
  **INVOCATION SEAM (ADR-015):** the engine (driver) decides *when / which* task to run;
  the actual Agent-in-worktree spawn is done by the thin harness **worker skill** — engine core never spawns.
  The seam abstracts `invokeClaudeCode(taskPrompt, worktree)`: ideal impl = `claude -p "<self-contained prompt>"`
  (one headless process/task); today's impl = one persistent interactive **seat + Monitor** multiplexing N such calls
  (billing-forced). **Monitor = invocation adapter, NOT scheduler/executor.** engine authors the prompt (payload);
  the adapter is prompt-agnostic transport. swap-litmus: engine output must drive EITHER a Monitor seat OR raw `claude -p`.
  **baime → epicd:** Monitor+scan-loop (2 hardcoded modes, 7 channels) ⇒ supervisor + **driver-per-pipeline**,
  channels DERIVED from (pipeline, phase, actor); `.agent-done` sentinel ⇒ **engine.complete()**;
  `.caps`/`.active-agents` ⇒ **Coordinator**; status-advance-as-claim ⇒ phase stable + separate claim.
end note
@enduml
